premise_source_doc_sentence: The Society of the Friends of the Constitution  (  Société des amis de la Constitution  )  , after 1792 renamed Society of the Jacobins , Friends of Freedom and Equality  (  Société des Jacobins , amis de la liberté et de l'égalité  )  , commonly known as the Jacobin Club  (  Club des Jacobins  )  or simply the Jacobins  (  -LSB- ʒa.kɔ.bɛ̃ -RSB- , -LSB- lang 'd ʒæ.kə.bɪnz -RSB-  )  , was the most famous and influential political club in the development of the French Revolution .
